                "Num":"171",
                "Lyrics":"<a id=\"title\">HYMN #171</a><div id=\"content\">My dear Redeemer and my Lord,<br/>I read my duty in thy Word;<br/>But in thy life the law appears<br/>Drawn out in living characters.<br/><br/>Such was thy truth, and such thy zeal,<br/>Such def'rence to thy Father's will,<br/>Such love, and meekness so divine,<br/>I would transcribe and make them mine.<br/><br/>Cold mountains and the midnight air<br/>Witnessed the fervor of thy prayer;<br/>The desert thy temptations knew,<br/>Thy conflict and thy vict'ry too.<br/><br/>Be thou my pattern; make me bear<br/>More of thy gracious image here:<br/>Then God the Judge shall own my name<br/>Amongst the foll'wers of the Lamb.<br/><br/>AMEN.</div>",
