                "Lyrics":"<a id=\"title\">HYMN #220</a><div id=\"content\">Blessed Jesus, at thy word<br/>We are gathered all to hear thee;<br/>Let our hearts and souls be stirred<br/>Now to seek and love and fear thee,<br/>By thy teachings, sweet and holy,<br/>Drawn from earth to love thee solely.<br/><br/>All our knowledge, sense, and sight<br/>Lie in deepest darkness shrouded<br/>Till thy Spirit breaks our night<br/>With the beams of truth unclouded.<br/>Thou alone to God canst win us;<br/>Thou must work all good within us.<br/><br/>Glorious Lord, thyself impart,<br/>Light of Light, from God proceeding;<br/>Open thou our ears and heart,<br/>Help us by thy Spirit's pleading;<br/>Hear the cry thy people raises,<br/>Hear and bless our prayers and praises.<br/><br/>Father, Son, and Holy Ghost,<br/>Praise to thee and adoration!<br/>Grant that we thy Word may trust<br/>And obtain true consolation<br/>While we here below must wander,<br/>Till we sing thy praises yonder.<br/><br/>AMEN.</div>",
