                "Num":"232",
                "Lyrics":"<a id=\"title\">HYMN #232</a><div id=\"content\">Light of the lonely pilgrim's heart,<br/>Star of the coming day,<br/>Arise, and with thy morning beams<br/>Chase all our griefs away.<br/><br/>Come, blessed Lord, bid ev'ry shore<br/>And answ'ring island sing<br/>The praises of thy royal Name,<br/>And own thee as their King.<br/><br/>Bid the whole earth, responsive now<br/>To the bright world above,<br/>Break forth in rapturous strains of joy<br/>In mem'ry of thy love.<br/><br/>Lord, Lord, thy fair creation groans,<br/>The air, the earth, the sea,<br/>In unison with all our hearts,<br/>And calls aloud for thee.<br/><br/>Come, then, with all thy quick'ning pow'r,<br/>With one awak'ning smile,<br/>And bid the serpent's trail no more<br/>Thy beauteous realms defile.<br/><br/>Thine was the cross, with all its fruits<br/>Of grace and peace Divine:<br/>Be thine the crown of glory now,<br/>The palms of vict'ry thine.<br/><br/>AMEN.</div>",
