                "Num":"422",
                "Lyrics":"<a id=\"title\">HYMN #423</a><div id=\"content\">Approach, my soul, the mercy-seat<br/>Where Jesus answers prayer;<br/>There humbly fall before his feet,<br/>For none can perish there.<br/><br/>Thy promise is my only plea;<br/>With this I venture nigh:<br/>Thou callest burdened souls to thee,<br/>And such, O Lord, am I.<br/><br/>Bowed down beneath a load of sin,<br/>By Satan sorely pressed,<br/>By war without, and fears within,<br/>I come to thee for rest.<br/><br/>Be thou my shield and hiding place,<br/>That, sheltered near thy side,<br/>I may my fierce accuser face,<br/>And tell him, thou hast died.<br/><br/>O wondrous love! to bleed and die,<br/>To bear the cross and shame,<br/>That guilty sinners, such as I,<br/>Might plead thy gracious Name!<br/><br/>AMEN.</div>",
