                "HymnalID":2,
                "Num":"668",
                "Lyrics":"<a id=\"title\">HYMN #668</a><div id=\"content\">Far and near the fields are teeming<br/>With the waves of ripened grain;<br/>Far and near their gold is gleaming<br/>O'er the sunny slope and plain.<br/><br/>Refrain:<br/>Lord of harvest, send forth reapers!<br/>Hear us, Lord, to thee we cry;<br/>Send them now the sheaves to gather,<br/>Ere the harvest time pass by.<br/><br/>Send them forth with morn's first beaming,<br/>Send them in the noontide's glare;<br/>When the sun's last rays are gleaming,<br/>Bid them gather ev'rywhere.<br/><br/>Refrain:<br/>Lord of harvest, send forth reapers!<br/>Hear us, Lord, to thee we cry;<br/>Send them now the sheaves to gather,<br/>Ere the harvest time pass by.<br/><br/>O thou, whom thy Lord is sending,<br/>Gather now the sheaves of gold;<br/>Heav'nward then at evening wending,<br/>Thou shalt come with joy untold.<br/><br/>Refrain:<br/>Lord of harvest, send forth reapers!<br/>Hear us, Lord, to thee we cry;<br/>Send them now the sheaves to gather,<br/>Ere the harvest time pass by.<br/><br/>AMEN.</div>",
