                "Lyrics":"<a id=\"title\">HYMN #631</a><div id=\"content\">Shine thou upon us, Lord,<br/>True Light of men, today,<br/>And through the written Word<br/>Thy very self display,<br/>That so from hearts which burn<br/>With gazing on thy face<br/>Thy little ones may learn<br/>The wonders of thy grace.<br/><br/>Breathe thou upon us, Lord,<br/>Thy Spirit's living flame,<br/>That so with one accord<br/>Our lips may tell thy name.<br/>Give thou the hearing ear,<br/>Fix thou the wandering thought,<br/>That those we teach may hear<br/>The great things thou hast wrought.<br/><br/>Speak thou for us, O Lord,<br/>In all we say of thee;<br/>According to thy Word<br/>Let all our teaching be,<br/>That so thy lambs may know<br/>Their own true Shepherd's voice,<br/>Where'er he leads them go,<br/>And in his love rejoice.<br/><br/>Live thou within us, Lord;<br/>Thy mind and will be ours;<br/>Be thou belov'd, adored,<br/>And served with all our powers,<br/>That so our lives may teach<br/>Thy children what thou art,<br/>And plead, by more than speech,<br/>For thee with ev'ry heart.<br/><br/>AMEN.</div>",
