                "Lyrics":"<a id=\"title\">HYMN #637</a><div id=\"content\">God, who made the earth,<br/>The air, the sky, the sea,<br/>Who gave the light its birth,<br/>Careth for me.<br/><br/>God who made the grass,<br/>The flow'r, the fruit, the tree,<br/>The day and night to pass,<br/>Careth for me.<br/><br/>God who made the sun,<br/>The moon, the stars, is he<br/>Who, when life's clouds come on,<br/>Careth for me.<br/><br/>God who made all things,<br/>On earth, in air, in sea,<br/>Who changing seasons brings,<br/>Careth for me.<br/><br/>God who sent his Son<br/>To die on Calvary,<br/>He, if I lean on him,<br/>Will care for me.<br/><br/>When in heav'n's bright land<br/>I all his loved ones see,<br/>I'll sing with that blest band,<br/>God cared for me.<br/><br/>AMEN.</div>",
