                "Lyrics":"<a id=\"title\">HYMN #656</a><div id=\"content\">Ye children, come, give ear to me<br/>And learn Jehovah's fear;<br/>He who would long and happy live,<br/>Let him my counsel hear.<br/><br/>Refrain:<br/>Children, come, hither come,<br/>And unto me give ear,<br/>I shall you teach to understand<br/>How ye the Lord should fear.<br/><br/>Restrain thy lips from speaking guile,<br/>From wicked speech depart,<br/>From evil turn and do the good,<br/>Seek peace with all thy heart.<br/><br/>Refrain:<br/>Children, come, hither come,<br/>And unto me give ear,<br/>I shall you teach to understand<br/>How ye the Lord should fear.<br/><br/>Jehovah's eyes are on the just,<br/>He hearkens to their cry;<br/>Against the wicked sets his face,<br/>Their very name shall die.<br/><br/>Refrain:<br/>Children, come, hither come,<br/>And unto me give ear,<br/>I shall you teach to understand<br/>How ye the Lord should fear.<br/><br/>AMEN.</div>",
